abis</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v550/n7676/full/nature24270.html\">Mastering the game of Go without human knowledge</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nature_%28journal%29\">Nature</a>, Vol. 550, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.gwern.net/docs/rl/2017-silver.pdf\">pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/gcp/leela-zero\">GitHub - gcp/leela-zero: Go engine with no human-provided knowledge, modeled after the AlphaGo Zero paper</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=66280\">Announcing lczero</a> by <a href=\"/Gary_Linscott\" title=\"Gary Linscott\">Gary</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 09, 2018 </span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/glinscott/leela-chess\">GitHub - glinscott/leela-chess: A chess adaption of GCP's Leela Zero</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301082738\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.028 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.030 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 189/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 406/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\n